claim.claim-text:
1. A device comprising:
a set of sensors to monitor a surrounding area of a user of a mobility assistance device, wherein the mobility assistance device comprises a wheelchair, a walker, a cane, a crutch, or a prosthetic;
a processor to detect a hazard in the surrounding area, based on data from the set of sensors;
a first set of feedback mechanisms to provide the user with an alert that notifies the user of the hazard; and
a communication device to send a notification to a third party informing the third party of the hazard.

12. A method comprising:
monitoring a surrounding area of a user of a mobility assistance device, wherein the mobility assistance device comprises a wheelchair, a walker, a cane, a crutch, or a prosthetic;
detecting a hazard in the surrounding area, based on the monitoring;
providing the user with an alert that notifies the user of the hazard, in response to the detecting; and
sending a notification to a third party informing the third party of the hazard, in response to the detecting.

19. A non-transitory computer-readable storage medium storing instructions which, when executed by a processor, cause the processor to perform operations, the operations comprising:
monitoring a surrounding area of a user of a mobility assistance device, wherein the mobility assistance device comprises a wheelchair, a walker, a cane, a crutch, or a prosthetic;
detecting a hazard in the surrounding area, based on the monitoring;
providing the user with an alert that notifies the user of the hazard, in response to the detecting; and
sending a notification to a third party informing the third party of the hazard, in response to the detecting.
